Researchers at Yale University asked people if they believe global warming is happening and whether they are worried about the warming planet . 
  The interactive map reveals public opinion in all 50 states, 435 congressional districts and more than 3,000 counties . 
  Nationally, 52 per cent of Americans are worried by global warming . 
  Concern about global warming ranges from 38 per cent in Tennessee to a high of 74 in Washington, D . 
 C . 
  Hawaii, California, Vermont and Massachusetts are the four states that are most worried . 
  But opinions on global warming vary wildly between states . 
  People in California are far more worried about warming than those in the central US . 
  Just over 60 per cent believe the planet is warming and half blame humans . 
 